Significant differences were observed in values of red blood cell counts, hemoglobin and hematocrit for dogs of group A compared to those of groups B and control (Fig. 2
), principally at 15 p.i. (p
 ≤ 0.05). The hematimetric indices of MGV, MGH and MGHC did not present significant differences.

The mean values of immature neutrophils of group B were significantly greater than those of the groups A and control at 15, 60, 75 and 165 p.i. (p
 ≤ 0.05) although no differences were seen for segmented neutrophils (Fig. 3
).

The mean values of eosinophils in dogs of groups A and B (Fig. 4
) were both significantly higher than those of the control group at 120, 135 and 165 p.i. (p
 ≤ 0.05).
